\begin_layout Chapter
Analysis Strategy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The core of this analysis is the measurement of the top quark spin asymmetries.
 The analysis strategy can be divided into the following two steps which
 are described in detail in this chapter:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Measurement of the single top quark t-channel differential 
\begin_inset Formula ${\textstyle \frac{\mathrm{d}\sigma}{\mathrm{d}\cos\theta_{\mathrm{B,\, X}}}}$
\end_inset

 distributions.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{X}$
\end_inset

 denotes the spin analyzer (muon, b-tagged jet, or neutrino) and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{B}$
\end_inset

 denotes the spin basis (spectator or beamline).
 Multivariate analysis techniques are used to separate signal and background
 events.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Unfolding of the distributions to correct for reconstruction and detector
 effects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the unfolded distributions the top quark spin asymmetries are calculated.
\end_layout

