\end_inset

 shows the first and the 100th variable in the histogram 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 against the 
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\theta_{\mathrm{spec.,\, muon}}$
\end_inset

 angle.
 For the first variable, no obvious correlation is visible.
 The 100th variable presents a slight correlation because the regions around
 the points 
\begin_inset Formula $(1.0,\,0.0)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(0.0,\,1.0)$
\end_inset

