\end_inset

A perfect detector (
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon=1$
\end_inset

) does not have any artificial correlations.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon<1$
\end_inset

, the unfolded distribution is dominated by negative correlations between
